snippet.textDisplay:
That awkward moment when you realize an entire room of people just had a visceral reaction and became hostile towards a single individual in the room, but you are quite certain none of them would actually be able to articulate why if asked.

I grow tired of this bullshit, always pretending like everything is racist. News flash, kids bully each other, and the little shits are quite happy to use whatever you are most sensitive about to do it. If you whine like petulant child every time someone uses the word "spick", then guess what... you might want to get used to it, because the bullies will just use it more, because it works.

And yea, the thing about bullies is they aim to offend you, so whether they are racist or not, they are gonna pull out all the stops to do it. Just because somebody used a racial slur, doesn't actually mean they are a racist, it means they wanted to insult you, and frankly you make it easy by having this subset of magic words that apparently just wound you beyond all comparison.

Today on the drive to work I saw two other drivers have a dispute over one cutting the other off. The person who got cut off called the other a racial epithet starting with the letter N (you know that word we treat like Voldemort from Harry Potter for some bizarre reason). Do I think that driver was racist or hates black people? Maybe, I don't know, he may or he may not. What I do know is he had about a tenth of a second to utter that one word he could think of that would just stay on that asshole's mind all day long, and I gotta say, that's they one that might do it.
